-- PRESS DIGEST - RUSSIA - June 6
-- 
-- Fri Jun 06, 2014 03:29AM EDT
-- None



MOSCOW, June 6 (Reuters) - The following are some of the leading stories in Russia's newspapers on Friday. Reuters has not verified these stories and does not vouch for their accuracy.

VEDOMOSTI www.vedomosti.ru - Russia will ratify an OECD convention on tax assistance, the daily says, after the cabinet directed a draft bill to the  lower chamber of parliament for approval. - The construction of a bridge over the Kerch strait linking Crimea and Russia's mainland could cost at least 300 billion roubles ($8.55 billion), according to experts. - Russia's state-controlled Sberbank <SBER.MM> has again raised interest rates for corporate loans. This will further slow down economic development, the daily says.   KOMMERSANT www.kommersant.ru - Rosneft <ROSN.MM> president Igor Sechin said on Thursday the state oil major would invest $400 billion in development of  Arctic oil and gas fields over the next 20 years. - Russia needs almost 140 billion roubles ($4 billion) to reform Crimea's energy grids but has so far failed to decide on how to source investments into the project. - Deputy Prime Minister Dmitry Rogozin has urged the government to speed up the process of placing state military orders with Crimean enterprises.  ROSSIISKAYA GAZETA www.rg.ru